2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a new link layer security scheme in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new technique for data authentication and privacy in a faster and scalable way, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may also fall under the category of software engineering as it proposes a new technique for implementing security in wireless sensor networks. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper may also have implications for the societal impact of wireless sensor networks, as security is a critical issue in many applications of WSNs.
